      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here's a draft abstract that should help you make a strong impression:\n\n\"Recursive logic processing in large language models (LLMs) is a paradigmatic example of the intricate interplay between cognitive architectures and computational constraints. Our pilot study, conducted with a modest sample of 10 participants and 10 instances, reveals a striking ceiling effect in LLMs' ability to navigate nested logical structures. Specifically, we found that LLMs exhibit a pronounced limitation in their capacity to process recursive logic tasks beyond a depth of three, underscoring the notion of a fundamental cognitive bottleneck in these models. These findings have significant implications for our understanding of the cognitive and computational limitations of LLMs, and highlight the need for further research into the development of more robust and general-purpose logical reasoning architectures.\"",
